Input: Subset of agents $N^{\prime}\subseteq N$ , metric $d$ , threshold integer $\tau$   
Output: Cluster $S$   
if $|N^{\prime}|\leqslant\tau$ then return $S\gets N^{\prime}$ ;   
for $i\in N^{\prime}$ do $\ell_{i}\gets\tau$ -th closest agent in $N^{\prime}$ to agent $i$ ; // Ties are broken arbitrarily $r_{i}\gets d(i,\ell_{i})$ ; // Smallest ball centered at agent $i$ capturing at least $\tau$ agents   
end   
i∗←arg mini∈N ′ ri;   
return $S\gets$ the set of $\tau$ closest agents in $N^{\prime}$ to agent $i^{*}$ ;

$$
\ell_{i}(S)={\left\{\begin{array}{l l}{\infty}&{{\mathrm{if~}}S=\{0,1,2\}{\mathrm{~or~}}3\in S,}\\ {1}&{{\mathrm{if~}}|S|=2{\mathrm{~and~}}i+1{\mathrm{~mod~}}3\notin S,}\\ {0}&{{\mathrm{if~}}S=\{i,i+1{\mathrm{~mod~}}3\}.}\end{array}\right.}
$$

$$
\begin{array}{l}{\displaystyle\ell_{i^{*}}(C(i^{*}))=\frac{1}{|C(i^{*})|}\sum_{i\in C(i^{*})}{d(i^{*},i)}}\\ {\displaystyle\leqslant\frac{1}{|C(i^{*})|}\left(d(i^{*},i^{\prime})+\sum_{i\in C(i^{*})\backslash\{i^{\prime},i^{*}\}}\left(d(i^{*},i^{\prime})+d(i^{\prime},i)\right)\right)}\\ {\displaystyle\leqslant\left(2-\frac{3}{\lceil n/k\rceil}\right)\cdot R.}\end{array}
$$
